1
00:00:05,902 --> 00:00:07,236
我相信你最近在各种内容下面
I'm sure you've seen comments like this all over the internet lately.

2
00:00:07,236 --> 00:00:09,672
应该都见过这样一句类似的评论
I'm sure you've seen comments like this all over the internet lately.

3
00:00:09,672 --> 00:00:10,707
那几个月之前
A few months ago,

4
00:00:10,707 --> 00:00:12,608
其实大家把这个当成一种调侃了
people mostly said it as a joke,

5
00:00:12,608 --> 00:00:13,776
是一种梗 对吧
like a meme, right?

6
00:00:13,776 --> 00:00:15,078
你看到太离谱的东西
When you saw something ridiculous,

7
00:00:15,078 --> 00:00:16,212
你会说
you'd say,

8
00:00:16,212 --> 00:00:19,182
哎呀这是AI或者AI太好用了家人
"Come on, that's AI," or "AI is way too good now, folks."

9
00:00:19,182 --> 00:00:21,250
但有意思就是只过了短短几个月
But what's interesting is that in just a few short months,

10
00:00:21,250 --> 00:00:22,952
你会发现现在这句 这是AI吗
the question, "Is this AI?"

11
00:00:22,952 --> 00:00:24,187
背后的情绪
has taken on a completely different feeling.

12
00:00:24,187 --> 00:00:25,722
它变化了
has taken on a completely different feeling.

13
00:00:25,722 --> 00:00:27,390
因为AI它又变强了
Because AI has gotten even better.

14
00:00:27,390 --> 00:00:28,925
所以现在互联网内容消费环境
So I think the way we consume content online now

15
00:00:28,925 --> 00:00:30,093
我觉得开始进入一种
is starting to feel like

16
00:00:30,093 --> 00:00:32,562
抓狐狸尾巴的状态
a constant game of spotting the fox's tail.

17
00:00:32,562 --> 00:00:34,263
那我说的不只是国内
And I'm not just talking about China,

18
00:00:34,263 --> 00:00:36,065
而是全球内容消费者
I mean content consumers worldwide.

19
00:00:36,065 --> 00:00:37,533
我自己也是这个消费者
I'm one of them too.

20
00:00:37,533 --> 00:00:38,768
你有没有过近似的体验
Have you ever had an experience like this?

21
00:00:38,768 --> 00:00:40,336
就是你点开一个新的内容
You click on a new piece of content,

22
00:00:40,336 --> 00:00:43,139
现在你可能根本没在关注内容本身
and instead of paying attention to the content itself,

23
00:00:43,139 --> 00:00:45,141
而是在看背景里的文字有没有扭曲
you're looking for warped text in the background,

24
00:00:45,141 --> 00:00:46,976
数人手上有几根手指
counting how many fingers someone in the video has,

25
00:00:46,976 --> 00:00:48,544
尝试辨别
trying to figure out,

26
00:00:48,544 --> 00:00:50,880
这到底是不是由一台电脑
is this actually a computer-made

27
00:00:50,880 --> 00:00:53,983
做给我的所谓的真人的真实视频
so-called real video of a real person made for me?

28
00:00:53,983 --> 00:00:54,650
可是另一方面
But on the other hand,

29
00:00:54,650 --> 00:00:56,019
我自己也是做视频的人
I make videos too.

30
00:00:56,019 --> 00:00:57,086
我挺希望观众
And I really hope viewers

31
00:00:57,086 --> 00:00:58,988
不是这样来看我们的内容
aren't watching our content that way.

32
00:00:58,988 --> 00:01:00,990
因为情绪就完全混乱了
Because it completely scrambles the emotional experience.

33
00:01:00,990 --> 00:01:03,159
所以是一个超级矛盾的状态
So it's an incredibly contradictory situation.

34
00:01:03,159 --> 00:01:05,194
但这就是我们这个视频想来和你聊的
And that's exactly what we want to talk about in this video.

35
00:01:05,194 --> 00:01:07,330
在2026年中段这个时间
Here in the middle of 2026,

36
00:01:07,330 --> 00:01:10,299
我觉得AI已经强到了一个地步
I think AI has become so powerful

37
00:01:10,299 --> 00:01:12,502
它开始进入快速摧毁
that it's entering a phase of rapidly eroding trust

38
00:01:12,502 --> 00:01:13,970
互联网信任的阶段
on the internet.

39
00:01:13,970 --> 00:01:16,472
那首先讨厌或者质疑AI的情绪
First, the dislike of AI, or skepticism toward AI

40
00:01:16,472 --> 00:01:17,673
其实很好理解
is pretty easy to understand.

41
00:01:17,673 --> 00:01:20,209
因为AI内容很容易被关联到两个词上
Because AI-generated content is often associated with two things:

42
00:01:20,209 --> 00:01:21,744
就是劣质和偷懒
low quality and laziness.

43
00:01:21,744 --> 00:01:24,113
那我不是说现在没有好的AI内容
I'm not saying there's no good AI content out there.

44
00:01:24,113 --> 00:01:25,081
你说做得好的
There are good ones,

45
00:01:25,081 --> 00:01:27,116
像这种很有想法的AI短片
like these creative AI shorts,

46
00:01:27,116 --> 00:01:28,584
还有这种水果短剧
or these fruit-themed mini dramas,

47
00:01:28,584 --> 00:01:30,119
你不能说它不好 对吧
you can't really say they're bad, right?

48
00:01:30,119 --> 00:01:31,888
确实很搞笑也很魔性
They're genuinely funny and weirdly addictive.

49
00:01:31,888 --> 00:01:32,655
我也看
I watch them too.

50
00:01:32,655 --> 00:01:34,357
但是这些AI内容之所以受欢迎
But the reason these AI videos are popular

51
00:01:34,357 --> 00:01:36,526
是因为作者借助AI这个工具
is because their creators used AI as a tool

52
00:01:36,526 --> 00:01:38,327
花费了大量的精力去打磨
and put a huge amount of effort into refining them,

53
00:01:38,327 --> 00:01:39,629
是值得敬佩的
which deserves respect.

54
00:01:39,629 --> 00:01:41,130
但是毕竟好的内容是少数
But good content is still the minority.

55
00:01:41,130 --> 00:01:43,900
大部分目前我们看到的AI作品是这种
Most of the AI content we see right now looks more like this:

56
00:01:43,900 --> 00:01:45,468
乱七八糟的文字
nonsensical text,

57
00:01:45,468 --> 00:01:47,136
错误的视频信息
incorrect visual information.

58
00:01:47,136 --> 00:01:47,904
比如你看这个
Take this for example.

59
00:01:47,904 --> 00:01:50,006
这个俯卧撑 手都飞到另一边去了
For the push-up image, the hands are flying to the sky.

60
00:01:50,006 --> 00:01:51,607
这是绝对侮辱我们的智商
That's an insult to our intelligence.

61
00:01:51,607 --> 00:01:53,009
那当然该骂
Of course it's a shame.

62
00:01:53,009 --> 00:01:54,777
对吧 这完全应该
Totally, right?

63
00:01:54,777 --> 00:01:56,212
但这是之前的情况
But that was the situation before.

64
00:01:56,212 --> 00:01:58,081
因为我们分得出来什么是AI
Because we could tell what was AI,

65
00:01:58,081 --> 00:02:00,083
所以我们可以骂或者不看
so we could mock it or just ignore it.

66
00:02:00,083 --> 00:02:01,384
但就是最近这五个月
But over the last five months or so,

67
00:02:01,384 --> 00:02:02,985
AI它进化了
AI has evolved.

68
00:02:02,985 --> 00:02:05,321
比如这两张图片放在一起
Now, if I put these two images side by side,

69
00:02:05,321 --> 00:02:08,724
你能分清楚哪个是AI的聊天记录吗
can you tell which WeChat screenshot was generated by AI?

70
00:02:08,724 --> 00:02:10,426
那么好 我们公布答案
Alright, here's the answer.

71
00:02:10,426 --> 00:02:12,328
左边这个是伪造的
The left one is fake.

72
00:02:12,328 --> 00:02:16,165
你可能以为AI是伪造了聊天软件的界面这个图片
You might think AI just faked the WeChat interface in that image.

73
00:02:16,165 --> 00:02:18,334
但事实上这整个图
But in reality, the entire picture,

74
00:02:18,334 --> 00:02:20,970
就这整个图包括指纹 这个手机
the fingerprint smudges on the screen, the phone itself,

75
00:02:20,970 --> 00:02:22,505
没有一个是真的
none of it is real.

76
00:02:22,505 --> 00:02:23,740
这就变得非常奇怪了
And that's the weird part.

77
00:02:23,740 --> 00:02:25,208
哪怕你再有经验
No matter how experienced you are,

78
00:02:25,208 --> 00:02:27,043
你很难一眼分辨出来
it's hard to tell at a glance

79
00:02:27,043 --> 00:02:28,978
这样的视频 这样的图片
whether a video or an image like this,

80
00:02:28,978 --> 00:02:30,346
是不是AI
was made by AI.

81
00:02:30,346 --> 00:02:31,180
我都不确定
If I'm not sure myself,

82
00:02:31,180 --> 00:02:33,416
那我该怎么表达我的情绪呢
how am I supposed to react?

83
00:02:33,416 --> 00:02:34,851
那这个时候我们唯一能做的就是
At that point, the only thing we can do

84
00:02:34,851 --> 00:02:36,252
不管看到什么
is ask ourselves, no matter what we see:

85
00:02:36,252 --> 00:02:37,420
好像都得先问一句
is ask ourselves, no matter what we see:

86
00:02:37,420 --> 00:02:38,721
这是AI吗
"Is this AI?"

87
00:02:38,721 --> 00:02:40,189
我们都开始不由自主地
We've all started, almost unconsciously,

88
00:02:40,189 --> 00:02:42,191
不再信任互联网上的内容
to stop trusting what we see online.

89
00:02:42,191 --> 00:02:44,460
是那种非常底层的不信任
And I mean a very fundamental kind of distrust,

90
00:02:44,460 --> 00:02:46,662
就是一个像素都不能信的那种
the kind where you don't trust a single pixel.

91
00:02:46,662 --> 00:02:47,363
但恰恰好
But the thing is,

92
00:02:47,363 --> 00:02:49,899
信任又是互联网上最大的杠杆
trust has always been the internet's biggest lever.

93
00:02:49,899 --> 00:02:51,000
一边是作者
Creators on one side,

94
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:52,602
另一边是观众和情绪
the other side are audiences and their emotions.

95
00:02:52,602 --> 00:02:53,870
大家能够平衡好了
When that balance works,

96
00:02:53,870 --> 00:02:55,371
大家都会很开心
everyone can be happy.

97
00:02:55,371 --> 00:02:57,707
你只有相信这是一个人认真拍的东西
You only feel moved if you believe a real person made it sincerely.

98
00:02:57,707 --> 00:02:58,941
你才会感动
You only feel moved if you believe a real person made it sincerely.

99
00:02:58,941 --> 00:03:00,476
你相信这是一个人花了几年
You only admire someone's work

100
00:03:00,476 --> 00:03:01,677
研究出来的东西
when you believe they spent years

101
00:03:01,677 --> 00:03:03,079
你才会欣赏他
figuring it out.

102
00:03:03,079 --> 00:03:05,214
但如果现在我们脑子的第一情绪
But if the first thing that comes to mind now

103
00:03:05,214 --> 00:03:06,682
变成了疑问句
is a question mark,

104
00:03:06,682 --> 00:03:08,184
那有相当长的一段时间
then for a significant amount of time,

105
00:03:08,184 --> 00:03:10,219
我们是脱离作者的情绪的
we're disconnected from the creator's emotions.

106
00:03:10,219 --> 00:03:12,121
我们在甄别 在怀疑
We're analyzing, we're doubting.

107
00:03:12,121 --> 00:03:14,257
这是一种被动的解构
It's a kind of passive deconstruction.

108
00:03:14,257 --> 00:03:16,292
以前互联网信任建立真的很快的
Trust used to form really quickly on the internet.

109
00:03:16,292 --> 00:03:17,960
但现在这个支点在不断地后移
But now it's getting harder and harder to earn.

110
00:03:17,960 --> 00:03:19,228
不管是在你的内容上
Whether you're watching content

111
00:03:19,228 --> 00:03:20,830
还是评论区和人交流
or talking to people in the comments,

112
00:03:20,830 --> 00:03:22,732
你都在怀疑他是不是人
you're wondering if there's even a real person.

113
00:03:22,732 --> 00:03:24,934
就很多内容已经撬不动情绪了
Many content just can't trigger an emotional response anymore.

114
00:03:24,934 --> 00:03:26,302
而且更糟糕的是这种变化
And what's worse,

115
00:03:26,302 --> 00:03:27,570
不只是针对视频
this shift isn't limited to video,

116
00:03:27,570 --> 00:03:29,806
你要发现图片 文字
images, text,

117
00:03:29,806 --> 00:03:32,742
各种形态的都在经历一样的事情
every format is going through the same thing.

118
00:03:32,742 --> 00:03:34,110
做东西最爽的其实是
The best parts of creating something

119
00:03:34,110 --> 00:03:35,545
找到认可和知音
is finding people who truly get it.

120
00:03:35,545 --> 00:03:37,180
看到大家的互动和评论
Seeing people's reactions and comments,

121
00:03:37,180 --> 00:03:39,015
这种人感是很重要的
that human connection matters.

122
00:03:39,015 --> 00:03:41,617
可是如果评论里面充满了类似
But when the comments are filled with things like,

123
00:03:41,617 --> 00:03:42,919
这是AI做的
"This was made by AI,"

124
00:03:42,919 --> 00:03:45,054
为什么不标AI这样的评论
or "Why didn't you label this as AI?"

125
00:03:45,054 --> 00:03:47,490
但如果这恰好是一个真的用心
and the creator actually spent real effort,

126
00:03:47,490 --> 00:03:48,291
用手工
working by hand,

127
00:03:48,291 --> 00:03:50,126
花了AI上千倍时间
spending a thousand times longer than AI would,

128
00:03:50,126 --> 00:03:51,727
做了内容的创作者
to make that piece of content,

129
00:03:51,727 --> 00:03:53,262
本来期待能找到有共鸣的观众
hoping it would resonate with people,

130
00:03:53,262 --> 00:03:55,298
看到这样的疑问句
seeing those kinds of comments,

131
00:03:55,298 --> 00:03:56,999
你说不难受是假的
of course it hurts.

132
00:03:56,999 --> 00:03:59,001
但这根本就不是观众的问题
But this really isn't the audience's fault.

133
00:03:59,001 --> 00:04:00,436
只是因为AI太像人了
It's that AI has become too human-like.

134
00:04:00,436 --> 00:04:02,672
创作的正向循环正在被快速削弱
The positive feedback loop of creation is being weakened quickly.

135
00:04:02,672 --> 00:04:05,341
AI和真人的产效差距又太大
And the productivity gap between AI and humans is becoming enormous.

136
00:04:05,341 --> 00:04:06,709
这对手工的作者
For creators who do things by hand,

137
00:04:06,709 --> 00:04:08,811
就是有点绝望的事情
that can feel pretty hopeless.

138
00:04:08,811 --> 00:04:11,247
尤其是现在的第二代模型
Especially with the second generation of models today.

139
00:04:11,247 --> 00:04:12,415
我不知道你没有了解过
I don't know if you've been following this stuff,

140
00:04:12,415 --> 00:04:13,583
我是这么叫它的
that's what I call them.

141
00:04:13,583 --> 00:04:16,519
它们开始渗透进入所有的软件里面了
They're starting to make their way into every piece of software.

142
00:04:16,519 --> 00:04:18,521
传统的这些大的软件
A lot of the traditional major apps

143
00:04:18,521 --> 00:04:21,357
反而变成了这些AI模型的插件
have almost become plugins for AI models instead.

144
00:04:21,357 --> 00:04:23,960
这使得AI把整个学习曲线给拆掉了
And that has basically flattened the entire learning curve.

145
00:04:23,960 --> 00:04:24,961
你不需要懂软件
No need to learn software,

146
00:04:24,961 --> 00:04:25,995
你只要会说话
you can just use voice commands.

147
00:04:25,995 --> 00:04:27,263
比如现在我对AI说
Like, I can tell an AI,

148
00:04:27,263 --> 00:04:28,764
给我做这样一个东西
make something like this for me.

149
00:04:28,764 --> 00:04:29,498
然后你看
And then,

150
00:04:29,498 --> 00:04:30,933
接下来这些过程
every process is done by the AI controlling the computer.

151
00:04:30,933 --> 00:04:33,336
全部都是由它操纵电脑完成的
every process is done by the AI controlling the computer.

152
00:04:33,336 --> 00:04:34,036
我得强调一下
I have to emphasize,

153
00:04:34,036 --> 00:04:36,372
我一个事都没做
that I didn't do anything.

154
00:04:36,372 --> 00:04:37,907
那如果AI自己会装软件
If AI can install and operate software on its own,

155
00:04:37,907 --> 00:04:38,674
会操作软件
If AI can install and operate software on its own,

156
00:04:38,674 --> 00:04:40,910
那我为什么还要学软件
why would I need to learn?

157
00:04:40,910 --> 00:04:41,611
那老实说
Honestly,

158
00:04:41,611 --> 00:04:43,145
这确实没什么问题
there's nothing wrong with that.

159
00:04:43,145 --> 00:04:44,046
这也是好事啊
It's a good thing.

160
00:04:44,046 --> 00:04:44,914
时代在进步
Technology is moving forward.

161
00:04:44,914 --> 00:04:45,915
你可能会说Tim
You might say, "Tim,

162
00:04:45,915 --> 00:04:47,283
你们从业者就是想要有壁垒
people in your industry just want barriers to entry.

163
00:04:47,283 --> 00:04:49,318
让你学的知识显得有价值
You want the knowledge you've learned to stay valuable."

164
00:04:49,986 --> 00:04:51,220
也可以这么理解吧
That's a fair way to look at it.

165
00:04:51,220 --> 00:04:52,688
谁不希望自己的作品有价值
Who doesn't want their work to have value?

166
00:04:52,688 --> 00:04:54,690
哪怕是AI生成的你生的
Even if something was generated by AI,

167
00:04:54,690 --> 00:04:57,260
你也会希望你生成的东西有价值
you'd still want what you created to have value.

168
00:04:57,260 --> 00:04:58,461
但我们仔细想想
But think about it for a second.

169
00:04:58,461 --> 00:05:00,029
如果我可以这么快速地
If I can acquire a software skill that quickly,

170
00:05:00,029 --> 00:05:02,231
获得一个软件的技能
If I can acquire a software skill that quickly,

171
00:05:02,231 --> 00:05:03,299
别人不行吗
why can't everyone else?

172
00:05:03,299 --> 00:05:04,333
这就是很微妙的地方
And that's where things get tricky.

173
00:05:04,333 --> 00:05:06,035
一旦通用型AI
Once general-purpose AI

174
00:05:06,035 --> 00:05:07,603
开始接管软件
starts taking over software,

175
00:05:07,603 --> 00:05:09,405
就是各行各业的软件
I mean software across every industry,

176
00:05:09,405 --> 00:05:10,673
它会改变一件事
it changes one thing:

177
00:05:10,673 --> 00:05:11,707
就是我们所有人
all of us

178
00:05:11,707 --> 00:05:13,676
未来都会更质疑每一个作品
will become more skeptical of every piece of work.

179
00:05:13,676 --> 00:05:15,611
因为一个底层的点被动了
Because something fundamental has changed:

180
00:05:15,611 --> 00:05:16,812
可复制性
replicability.

181
00:05:16,812 --> 00:05:18,147
以前一个作品做得好
Before, if someone made something great,

182
00:05:18,147 --> 00:05:18,948
别人最多只能
the most others could do was slowly replicate it by hand.

183
00:05:18,948 --> 00:05:20,416
慢慢手工地模仿
the most others could do was slowly replicate it by hand.

184
00:05:20,416 --> 00:05:21,751
但现在可以这样操作
But now it works like this:

185
00:05:21,751 --> 00:05:22,918
把这个火的作品
Take a viral piece of content,

186
00:05:22,918 --> 00:05:25,288
不管是真人做的还是AI做的
whether it was made by a person or by AI,

187
00:05:25,288 --> 00:05:26,122
交给AI
feed it to an AI,

188
00:05:26,122 --> 00:05:27,089
然后我们和它说
and tell it,

189
00:05:27,089 --> 00:05:28,858
帮我反推提示词
"Reverse-engineer the prompt for me."

190
00:05:28,858 --> 00:05:30,026
然后一分钟之后
A minute later,

191
00:05:30,026 --> 00:05:33,129
你的作品就被拆解成了文字和提示词
your work has been broken down into text and prompts.

192
00:05:33,129 --> 00:05:34,463
然后这时候你说
Then you say,

193
00:05:34,463 --> 00:05:35,865
帮我生成
"Generate something similar, but not exactly the same."

194
00:05:35,865 --> 00:05:38,301
一个近似但又不同的作品
"Generate something similar, but not exactly the same."

195
00:05:38,301 --> 00:05:38,968
就出现了
Then it appears.

196
00:05:38,968 --> 00:05:41,671
这也就是说一个人投入精力制作的原创内容
So, original content that someone spent real effort creating

197
00:05:41,671 --> 00:05:43,572
可以快速被一个智能体所理解
can now be quickly understood,

198
00:05:43,572 --> 00:05:44,173
提取
extracted,

199
00:05:44,173 --> 00:05:45,007
并且使用
and reused by an AI agent.

200
00:05:45,007 --> 00:05:47,109
然后再被上万个营销号
Then thousands of content farms

201
00:05:47,109 --> 00:05:49,645
分身出无数个近似的作品
can spin off countless similar versions.

202
00:05:49,645 --> 00:05:51,347
那原作真的能够
So can the original creator

203
00:05:51,347 --> 00:05:53,015
抢到应有的关注吗
still get the attention they deserve?

204
00:05:53,015 --> 00:05:53,849
不仅是视频
Not just about videos,

205
00:05:53,849 --> 00:05:54,750
建筑
architecture,

206
00:05:54,750 --> 00:05:55,818
文献
research papers,

207
00:05:55,818 --> 00:05:56,519
任何东西
anything

208
00:05:56,519 --> 00:05:57,920
都会遇到这样的状态
can end up in the same situation.

209
00:05:57,920 --> 00:05:58,454
那如果一个
And if a viewer

210
00:05:58,454 --> 00:06:00,656
已经看过AI复制品的观众
has already seen a bunch of AI copies,

211
00:06:00,656 --> 00:06:02,725
在终于刷到这个原创内容的时候
then finally comes across the original,

212
00:06:02,725 --> 00:06:04,226
是不是也会默认
won't they automatically

213
00:06:04,226 --> 00:06:07,029
打上AI生成这个标签了
assume it was AI-generated too?

214
00:06:07,029 --> 00:06:09,065
这会引申出更深的一个问题
That leads to an even deeper question.

215
00:06:09,065 --> 00:06:11,100
请问这个AI反推出来的作品
If this AI-reconstructed work was indeed created by this person,

216
00:06:11,100 --> 00:06:12,868
确实是由这个人操作的
If this AI-reconstructed work was indeed created by this person,

217
00:06:12,868 --> 00:06:14,170
这个作品的所属权
does ownership of the work really belong to them?

218
00:06:14,170 --> 00:06:15,838
真的属于这个作者吗
does ownership of the work really belong to them?

219
00:06:15,838 --> 00:06:17,006
这是原创吗
Is it original?

220
00:06:17,006 --> 00:06:18,007
我个人
Personally,

221
00:06:18,007 --> 00:06:20,009
感觉未来很多传统意义上的
I think a lot of what we traditionally consider

222
00:06:20,009 --> 00:06:21,010
原创版权
copyright and originality

223
00:06:21,010 --> 00:06:22,645
会被重新的定义
will end up being redefined.

224
00:06:22,645 --> 00:06:23,946
有一种可能性
One possibility,

225
00:06:23,946 --> 00:06:25,281
我觉得未来很有可能
and I think it's quite likely in the future,

226
00:06:25,281 --> 00:06:28,217
不存在原创和版权的概念
the concepts of originality and copyright may not even exist,

227
00:06:28,217 --> 00:06:30,319
只有肖像权和名誉权
what remains might just be rights of identity and reputation.

228
00:06:30,319 --> 00:06:33,022
因为从传统著作权来鉴定和维权
Because traditional copyright law is too hard to enforce.

229
00:06:33,022 --> 00:06:34,256
你会发现太难了
Because traditional copyright law is too hard to enforce.

230
00:06:34,256 --> 00:06:36,459
整个生产逻辑都已经变了
The entire production process has changed.

231
00:06:36,459 --> 00:06:38,260
就以前创作的本质是
Before, the essence of creation

232
00:06:38,260 --> 00:06:40,663
人和人经历产生的差异
came from differences in people's experiences.

233
00:06:40,663 --> 00:06:42,965
现在AI正在快速抹平这种差别
Now AI is rapidly erasing those differences.

234
00:06:42,965 --> 00:06:44,333
那该怎么办呢
So what do we do?

235
00:06:44,333 --> 00:06:45,534
答案是
The answer is:

236
00:06:45,534 --> 00:06:46,268
我不知道
I don't know.

237
00:06:46,268 --> 00:06:47,737
所以我做这个视频来和你讨论
That's why I made this video.

238
00:06:47,737 --> 00:06:49,205
国家其实响应很快的
Our country has responded pretty quickly.

239
00:06:49,205 --> 00:06:50,539
已经推出了很多条例
Many regulations have been introduced.

240
00:06:50,539 --> 00:06:51,640
这是绝对的好事
That's definitely a good thing.

241
00:06:51,640 --> 00:06:53,609
比如标注 还有平台监管
We have things like AI labeling and platform oversight.

242
00:06:53,609 --> 00:06:55,511
只能说AI现在有点太离谱了
All I can say is, AI has advanced so fast

243
00:06:55,511 --> 00:06:57,913
所以内容信任这件事 比较棘手
that trust in online content has become a really difficult problem.

244
00:06:57,913 --> 00:06:59,548
我很好奇你的想法
I'm curious about your ideas.

245
00:06:59,548 --> 00:07:02,118
这个互联网内容信任危机怎么办
How do we deal with this crisis of trust online?

246
00:07:02,118 --> 00:07:05,521
任何作品都可以被AI快速拆解重组
An era where AI can quickly break down and recreate any work,

247
00:07:05,521 --> 00:07:06,856
让人分不出真假
leaving people unable to tell what's real,

248
00:07:06,856 --> 00:07:10,459
只能留下评论“这是AI吗”的时代
and all they can ask is, "Is this AI?" seems to have arrived.

249
00:07:10,459 --> 00:07:12,595
好像已经来了
and all they can ask is, "Is this AI?" seems to have arrived.
